@davien.coffee  Rosemead SGV Peeps You already know because anything food or drink spreads like wild fire | Grand Opening. Set your alarms to wake up extra early for the amazing giveaways!

📆 Saturday, July 12th at 9AM

📍 8968 Garvey Ave Ste A, Rosemead, CA

🎁 First 350 in line get a FREE tote bag, steel tumbler, plushie, and a free drink voucher

One of my favorite Vietnamese coffee spot is now in San Gabriel Valley! ❤️

If you're in the SGV and a fan of Da Vien too, this means you and I both don't have to drive far when we're craving for Da Vien 🥰

Grand Opening for the Rosemead location is this Saturday, July 12th at 9 AM! The first 350 people in line will get a FREE tote bag, steel tumbler, plushie, and drink voucher 😇✨

The first time I had Da Vien, I was hooked! The drinks are soo good, Instagrammable, and affordable too. This Vietnamese coffee chain started in OC and has been making waves through SoCal, it's popular so it's usually busy! If you didn't know yet, there's an app so you can order your drinks online to save some time and avoid the lines 😌

Can't decide what to order? For a coffee drink, I recommend the Egg Cream Coffee, Ube Cream Coffee or the Marble Drip. My personal favorite is the Banana Matcha Latte and Coconut Matcha! 🍌🥥 Honestly, every drink I've tried at Da Vien didn't miss which is why Da Vien is one of my favorite coffee shops 🫶

Thank you for having me @davien.coffee 💌

📍Da Vien
8968 Garvey Ave, Ste A, Rosemead, CA 91770

@phoredbo_official just opened their new location at the Promenade in Rolling Hills and we stopped by for the soft opening! 😋🔥

Ever since I tried their OC locations, I’ve been a huge fan. Once you try their wagyu meat cuts, you’ll understand why they’re not your usual pho restaurant. The Bo Kho (beef stew) was super tender and packed with flavor which was perfect for dipping with that warm, crusty baguette. The Pho Dipped Banh Mi was a banger too, juicy and messy in the best way. We tried the Wagyu Fried Rice and Shaken Beef, and both came through with that signature RedBo quality.

If you’ve been rocking with their Westminster or Fountain Valley spots, you already know what time it is. Rolling Hills just got a serious upgrade. 🥢💯

📍 550 Deep Valley Dr, Ste 105, Rolling Hills Estates, CA

Want a FREE Bake & Che tote bag, steel tumbler and an Avocado Dessert Voucher?! Keep reading ✨

Bake & Che is having their Grand Opening this Saturday, July 5th at 9 AM! Save the date and be the one of the first 350 people in line and you'll get a tote bag, tumbler and dessert voucher for free 🫶

The popular OC Vietnamese dessert shop has finally made its way to SGV, serving fresh chè (sweet dessert beverage/soup), bánh (cake), and rau câu (jelly) daily using locally sourced fruits and premium ingredients! 

Don't know what to try? Order a 5-cake sampler to have a taste of all the bánh flavors and then order your chè depending on what ingredients you like! I'm a huge fan of the House Special and Chè Thái! House Special does contain durian which isn't for everyone but it is for me 😌❤️

Thank you for inviting me @bakeandche 💌

📍Bake & Che
8968 Garvey Ave, Unit B, Rosemead, CA 91770
